Google Translator¶

In [116]:
from googletrans import Translator
ls_t=[]
ls_translated=[]
def translate1(text):
    try:
        translator = Translator()
        ls_t.append(text)
        translated = translator.translate(text)
        ls_translated.append(translated.text)
        tx=translated.text
    except:
        tx=text
    return(tx)

Cleaning Tweets¶

In [248]:
# combine all the steps and create a udf
# takes one review as input and returns a cleaned review as a string
def  clean_txt(sent):
    tknzr = TweetTokenizer()
    tokens = tknzr.tokenize(sent.lower())
    stemmed = [lemm.lemmatize(term) for term in tokens 
               if term not in stop_updated and
               term not in list(punctuation) and len(term) > 2] 
    res = " ".join(stemmed)
    return res

stop_updated = stop_nltk + ["...","..","!!"]

from nltk.tokenize import regexp_tokenize
lemm=WordNetLemmatizer()
def clean_text2(sent):
    tokens = regexp_tokenize(sent,'#[\w]+')
    stemmed = [lemm.lemmatize(term,pos='v') for term in tokens\
              if term not in stop_nltk and \
              term not in list(punctuation) and \
              len(term) >2]
    res = " ".join(stemmed)
    return res
